# Project State Handoff

At the start of each substantial agent run, read `AGENTS.md` first, then read `docs/PROJECT_STATE.md` only when current status or implementation notes are needed.

After every major update, refresh `docs/PROJECT_STATE.md` before finishing. Keep it concise and factual:

- current status
- recently completed work
- known issues
- next recommended tasks
- important implementation notes

Do not turn the state file into a changelog. It should help the next agent resume without rediscovering the project.
Deep phase history belongs in implementation notes or dedicated validation / known-issues docs, not here.
